"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1943081-paralympics-cheating-row-explodes-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  A cheating row at this summer's Paralympic games in Paris has erupted with one athlete stripped of his medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 59, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998933617, \"rank\": 1.0668760092335344e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italian Giacomo Perini was disqualified from the final of the PR1 single sculls, with Australian Erik Horrie bumped up into the bronze medal position.\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 113, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9949198547232969, \"rank\": 0.0043087229042883726, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 199, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9971653905678359, \"rank\": 0.0024668236820961477, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 210, \"end\": 221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_Horrie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erik Horrie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_Horrie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_Horrie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Horrie joinedTeam GB'sBenjamin Pritchard and Ukrainian Roman Polianskyi on the podium, but it wasn't without controversy at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium in the French capital.\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language\", \"score\": 0.7262473237948359, \"rank\": 0.3705752466272529, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukrainian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.357236239101241e-14, \"text\": \"Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\"}, {\"begin\": 434, \"end\": 440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9914244401432271, \"rank\": 0.004777258785323555, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's claimed the Italian athlete was disqualified for using a communication device during the race, which is said to have been a mobile phone - something outlawed across the board at both the Paralympic and Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 468, \"end\": 475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9949198547232969, \"rank\": 0.0043087229042883726, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Race officials verified a device had been found and was used, with it then announced Perini had been booted out of the medal standings shortly after.\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An investigation has been launched by officials in Paris, with a statement released by World Rowing reading: \\\"In the final of the PR1 M1x, the ITA PR1 MRX was found to be using communications equipment during the race, in breach of Rule 28 and Appendix R2, Bye-Law to Rule 28.\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998933617, \"rank\": 1.0668760092335344e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Rowing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 955, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Runestone_styles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"PR1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Runestone_styles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Runestone_styles\"}, {\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"MRX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\"}, {\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"score\": 0.9869077597995988, \"rank\": 0.013217586509156271, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As a result, the crew has been excluded from the event and will be ranked last.\\\"\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy's rowing authority were next to chime in, claiming the rower had forgotten his phone had been left in the boat prior to the race starting.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9676678421415628, \"rank\": 0.03339398390468976, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A post shared by FederazioneItalianaCanottaggio (@canottaggio1888)  The governing body commented via anInstagrampost: \\\"After a historic and highly competitive competition, ending with an exciting third place and a bronze medal, while everyone was celebrating the achievement, the Jury was excluded from the Paralympic podium of the PR1 single for this reason: 'In the final Men's singles PR1, the Italian athlete was found using communication equipment during the race, in violation of rule 28 and Appendix R2, Bye-Law of rule 28.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1729, \"end\": 1736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9949198547232969, \"rank\": 0.0043087229042883726, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"score\": 0.9869077597995988, \"rank\": 0.013217586509156271, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_R\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Consequently, the crew was excluded from the event and is classified last.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They continued: \\\"The Federation is proceeding with an official claim, providing the records of Perini's phone, who is solely responsible for having forgotten it on the boat.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2114, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will shortly provide news of the outcome of the appeal.\\\"\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether it was a clumsy error or a legitimate ploy remains to be seen, but Horrie, the beneficiary from the scandal, insisted the rules are there to be followed.\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  On the error, the Aussie told native broadcaster Channel Nine: \\\"There was a situation that happened.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World Rowing and Paralympics officials saw it and then made the decision [to disqualify Perini] and I was lucky enough to come away with the bronze.\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Rowing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rowing_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's all I can say really.\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the joys of sport.\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are rules, and as athletes, we stick to them.\\\"\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2942, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3081, \"end\": 3094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1902147229962947e-16, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3130, \"end\": 3143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1902147229962947e-16, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"